The paper proposes a method for automatically generating image masks to train the Mask R-CNN deep learning method for object detection and segmentation. This involves the use of fully convolutional networks (FCN) for segmentation and Mask R-CNN for object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves deep learning methods and training, which could also place it in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
